com.googlecode.n_orm

Interface Process<Input>

  • Type Parameters:
    Input - The kind of elements to be processed. Should be a PersistingElement to be used in a search, or a Row to be used with ActionnableStore
    All Superinterfaces:
    Serializable
    All Known Implementing Classes:
    ProcessWrapper

    public interface Process<Input>
extends Serializable
    The interface for a process to be performed over an element. The main intent of this interface is to be used in conjunction with SearchableClassConstraintBuilder.forEach(Process), SearchableClassConstraintBuilder.remoteForEach(Process, Callback, int, long), Process.processElements(Class, com.googlecode.n_orm.storeapi.Constraint, Process, int, String[], int, ProcessCanceller, java.util.concurrent.ExecutorService), or Process.processElementsRemotely(Class, com.googlecode.n_orm.storeapi.Constraint, Process, Callback, int, String[], int, long). A process must have a default constructor (i.e. a constructor with no parameters).
